Program: Outlook
Title: 31/05/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00gvpjx
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 1 Jun 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Hasan Nuhanovic, the former UN translator whose entire family was killed during the massacre at Srebrenica in 1995, gives his reaction to the recent arrest of Ratko Mladic. Also in the programme, the extraordinary story of Hank Thomas, the Florida-born freedom rider who nearly lost his life 50 years ago when the bus he was travelling on was firebombed in Alabama. Show less